3 \\
-19
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{c}
0 \\
0 \\
0 \\
0 \\
0
\end{array}\right] </m>has (infinitely many) nontrivial solutions.</claim></li>
      <li> The set of vectors <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
-4 \\
4 \\
